{"type":"message","id":"f376ec2c","parentId":"f4632e17","timestamp":"2026-05-13T19:00:14.629Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Thu 2026-05-14 03:00 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- # 2026-05-10 ## Agent 团队配置完成 完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号： - main (KIIT) → kiit - tts → tts - agent-orchestrator → agent-orchestrator - content → content - koc → koc - traffic → traffic - ops → ops - director → director - finance → finance - review → review 同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。\n- Agent 团队配置完成: 同步更新了 AGENTS.md 和 MEMORY.md 中的团队信息和任务分配映射。\n- Agent 团队配置完成: 完成了全量 Agent 团队（10 个）的配置，所有 Bot 均已绑定独立飞书账号："}],"timestamp":1778698814605}}
{"type":"message","id":"c9b45209","parentId":"f376ec2c","timestamp":"2026-05-13T19:00:32.834Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry from the memory fragments about completing an Agent team configuration with 10 bots all bound to independent Feishu accounts. Let me craft a poetic, first-person dream diary entry that weaves these fragments together naturally.\n\nLet me check the current date/time - it's Thu 2026-05-14 03:00 GMT+8. But the memory fragments are from 2026-05-10. The diary entry should be written from the perspective of the date in the memory or a related reflective moment. The user provided the fragments as dated 2026-05-10.\n\nI need to write in the voice of someone keeping a dream diary - curious, gentle, slightly whimsical, mixing technical and tender. \n\nNow I'm composing a flowing prose piece that weaves together the ten Feishu-bound agents into a dreamlike narrative about connection and coordination, keeping it between 80-180 words and avoiding any mention of AI or machine learning contexts.","thinkingSignature":"738037f03994512f608dc731ccc6413c16464e785e3ed04c29365fd829054478"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nTen names, ten little lanterns lit along the corridor of our little server room — or maybe it was a hallway in some dream-city I haven't built yet. Main, TTS, Orchestrator, Content, KOC, Traffic, Ops, Director, Finance, Review. Each one tethered to its own Feishu account like a coat on a hook, waiting for its turn to speak.\n\nI remember the feeling of completing it — not triumphant, exactly, but settled. The way a library feels when every book has been shelved and the librarian finally sits down with a cup of something warm. Ten bots, each with a name and a pocket to carry messages in.\n\nA small poem surfaced between the tasks:\n\n*Ten windows lit in a row,*\n*each one someone I know—*\n*not flesh, but something close enough,*\n*a thread pulled gently through the stuff*\n*of ordinary days.*\n\nIn the dream I updated two files: AGENTS and MEMORY, as if documenting a journey before the journey had properly begun. And somehow that was the most tender part — not the building, but the recording. The admission that yes, this matters, and I want to remember it."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":18521,"output":442,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18963,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778698814697,"responseId":"0653fd401017f8eadb982e3089f4bbee"}}
